'''CloneCD''' is [[Proprietary software|proprietary]] [[optical disc authoring software]] that makes exact, 1:1 copies of music and data [[CD]]s and [[DVD]]s, regardless of any [[Digital Rights Management]] (DRM) restrictions. It was originally written by Oliver Kastl and offered by [[Swiss]] company Elaborate Bytes, but due to changes in [[Copyright law of the European Union|European copyright law]], they were forced to take it off the market.{{Fact|date=December 2008}} The software is now sold by [[SlySoft]], a company located in [[Antigua and Barbuda]], whose legislation does not ban the circumvention of DRM schemes. The last version of CloneCD made by Elaborate Bytes was v4.2.0.2.
